I would like to thank the following people and organizations for their
contribution to roar-ng:

 - noryb009, for translating the package list conversion scripts to awk and
   distribution support code.
 - Barry Kauler (www.bkhome.org), for creating Woof, the reason why roar-ng 
   exists.
 - Tomas M. (www.tomas-m.com), for writing the Linux Live scripts, another major
   source of inspiration for roar-ng.
 - Authors of the Arch Linux wiki, for providing useful information and 
   guidance.
 - Contributors of The Arch User Repository (AUR), for useful explanations,
   patches and inspiration.
 - 2byte from the Puppy Linux community, for an early hpm bug report.
